Can we reach 100K followers soon? Follow @iwillexplainn Explanation: Water gets inside a coconut through a process called osmosis. Initially, the coconut contains a liquid called endosperm, which is a nutrient-rich fluid. As the coconut matures, the endosperm gradually solidifies into the white, edible coconut meat, and the liquid inside becomes coconut water. This transformation occurs as the coconut absorbs water from the surrounding environment through its shell via osmosis. Checkout @iwillexplainn for all the posts that can be daily explained.
